[{"id":"FT546474","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p><img alt=\"The figure consists of a horizontal beam where the left end of the beam is attached to a vertical wall by a pivot and the right end of the beam is attached to a cable. The other end of the cable is above the beam and is attached near the top of the wall. The angle between the beam and the cable is labeled theta and on the cable is an arrow which points along the cable and towards the wall and is labeled T. There is an arrow pointing downwards from the midpoint of the beam and is labeled W.\" height=\"363\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/c56526352951f0f7afa7fc31d5649cf1/original.png\" width=\"250\" /></p>\n\n<p>A uniform beam of weight <em>W</em> is attached to a wall by a pivot at one end and is held horizontal by a cable attached to the other end of the beam and to the wall, as shown above. <em>T</em> is the tension in the cable, which makes an angle <em>θ</em> with the beam. Which of the following is equal to <em>T</em> ?</p>\n","choicesHtml":["<span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator cap w and denominator 2 cosine theta\"><math> <semantics> <mrow> <mfrac> <mi>W</mi> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mi>cos</mi> <mi>θ</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3F8B@</annotation> </semantics> </math></span>","<span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator cap w and denominator 2 sine theta\"><math> <semantics> <mrow> <mfrac> <mi>W</mi> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mi>sin</mi> <mi>θ</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3F90@</annotation> </semantics> </math></span>","<span aria-label=\"cap w over cosine theta\"><math> <semantics> <mrow> <mfrac> <mi>W</mi> <mrow> <mi>cos</mi> <mi>θ</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3ECF@</annotation> </semantics> </math></span>","<span aria-label=\"cap w over sine theta\"><math> <semantics> <mrow> <mfrac> <mi>W</mi> <mrow> <mi>sin</mi> <mi>θ</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3ED4@</annotation> </semantics> </math></span>","<p><em>W</em></p>"],"answer":0}]